        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 2:48PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 248 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near West Glens Falls to near Galway. Movement
was northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Parkis Mills, Lake Luzerne, West Milton, Greenfield Center, Wiley
Corners, Porter Corners, North Milton, Saratoga Race Course,
Danielstown, Glens Falls, East Hartford, South Corinth, Wilton,
Dimmick Corners, Fortsville, Hudson Falls, Clarks Corner, Durkeetown,
Fenimore, and Pages Corner.

This includes Interstate 87 between exits 13N and 22.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
east central New York.</instruction>
